---
import ComparisonPage from '@/components/astro/ComparisonPage.astro';
---

<ComparisonPage
  ogImage="https://www.digistorms.ai/og/compare-loops.webp"
  slug="digistorms-vs-loops"
  competitorName="Loops"
  competitorUrl="https://loops.so"
  competitorTagline="Email platform built for SaaS"
  title="DigiStorms vs Loops: Which SaaS Email Tool Is Right for You? (2026)"
  metaDescription="Compare DigiStorms and Loops for SaaS email. See how AI-generated onboarding sequences stack up against Loops' developer-first email platform."
  h1="DigiStorms vs Loops"
  subtitle="AI onboarding agent vs developer-first email platform"
  verdict="Loops is a powerful, developer-friendly email platform with beautiful templates and a clean API — a DIY tool your team configures and operates. DigiStorms is the opposite model: a done-for-you AI onboarding agent that analyzes your product, maps your activation milestones, then writes and runs a behavior-based sequence that turns signups into paying customers on autopilot. Choose Loops to build and run it yourself. Choose DigiStorms to have it done for you, tailored to your product, and tied to revenue — set up by a quick onboarding call."
  features={[
    { name: "AI sequence generation", digistorms: true, competitor: false },
    { name: "Done-for-you setup", digistorms: true, competitor: false },
    { name: "AI agent tailored to your product", digistorms: true, competitor: false },
    { name: "Developer API/SDK", digistorms: "Basic", competitor: "Full API + SDK" },
    { name: "Transactional emails", digistorms: false, competitor: true },
    { name: "Email library (1,000+ examples)", digistorms: true, competitor: "Small gallery" },
    { name: "DMARC/DKIM management", digistorms: false, competitor: true },
    { name: "Onboarding-specific features", digistorms: true, competitor: "General purpose" },
    { name: "Setup time", digistorms: "5 minutes", competitor: "30+ minutes" },
    { name: "npm package", digistorms: false, competitor: true },
    { name: "Template marketplace", digistorms: false, competitor: true },
  ]}
  pricingDigistorms="Custom — from $299/mo"
  pricingCompetitor="From $49/mo"
  pricingNote="Free tier for up to 100 contacts. Paid plans from $49/mo."
  faqs={[
    {
      question: "What's the real difference between DigiStorms and Loops?",
      answer: "Loops hands you a builder; DigiStorms hands you results. Loops is a self-serve email platform you configure and operate yourself — you design the flows, write the emails, and manage delivery. DigiStorms is a done-for-you AI onboarding agent: it analyzes your product, maps your activation milestones, then writes and runs a behavior-based sequence for you. With Loops you build it; with DigiStorms it's done for you and tied to activation and revenue.",
    },
    {
      question: "Is DigiStorms self-serve or done-for-you?",
      answer: "Done-for-you. There's nothing to configure yourself — DigiStorms builds and runs your onboarding sequence as a white-glove service, starting with a quick onboarding call where we map your product and activation goals. Loops, by contrast, is a self-serve platform you set up and operate in-house. DigiStorms pricing is custom, from $299/mo, and is built for teams serious about turning signups into paying customers.",
    },
    {
      question: "Is Loops better for developers?",
      answer: "Loops is built with developers in mind — it has a full API, SDK, npm package, and React Email support. If your team wants to code custom email flows and manage DMARC/DKIM directly, Loops provides more developer tooling. DigiStorms is designed for teams that want results without writing code — the AI generates your onboarding emails automatically.",
    },
    {
      question: "Which is better specifically for onboarding emails?",
      answer: "DigiStorms is purpose-built for SaaS onboarding and it's behavior-based, not time-based — it reacts to what users actually do, firing the next step when someone activates a feature, stalls, or hits a milestone. It analyzes your product, maps the activation journey, and writes and runs the sequence for you. Loops is a general-purpose email platform that can handle onboarding but requires you to design, build, and trigger every flow from scratch. For done-for-you onboarding tied to activation, DigiStorms is the more focused tool.",
    },
    {
      question: "Can I use both DigiStorms and Loops together?",
      answer: "Yes, they complement each other well. You could use DigiStorms to generate and optimize your onboarding sequences while using Loops for transactional emails and developer-triggered messages. Many SaaS teams use different tools for different email categories based on each tool's strengths.",
    },
    {
      question: "Who should choose Loops over DigiStorms?",
      answer: "Choose Loops if you have a developer-led team that wants full, hands-on control of your email stack. Loops offers a full API, SDK, npm package, React Email support, transactional email, and DMARC/DKIM management — ideal when you have engineering resources and want to build and operate custom flows yourself. Choose DigiStorms if you'd rather have your onboarding done for you: a tailored AI agent that maps your activation milestones and runs the sequence on autopilot, set up by a quick onboarding call instead of an in-house build.",
    },
    {
      question: "What integrations and channels does DigiStorms support?",
      answer: "DigiStorms connects to your product so its AI agent can react to real user behavior and trigger the right onboarding step at the right moment. It's focused on email today — there's no multi-channel SMS or push yet — and it's a newer, premium platform rather than a broad self-serve toolkit. If you need transactional email, a public API and SDK, or your own deliverability controls like DMARC/DKIM, Loops covers those directly.",
    },
  ]}
/>
